name: burger buns
source: https://www.joshuaweissman.com/recipes/best-burger-buns-recipe
yield: makes 6 buns, ~95-105g each
notes: |
  Brioche-milk bread hybrid bun. Tangzhong makes the crumb soft and pillowy.
components:
  - name: tangzhong
    ingredients:
      - item: whole milk
        mass: 60
      - item: water
        mass: 27
      - item: bread flour
        mass: 20
    steps:
      - whisk together in small saucepan
      - heat on medium, whisk constantly until thickened into a paste
      - set aside
  - name: dough
    ingredients:
      - item: whole milk
        mass: 120
        note: warm to 35°C
      - item: instant yeast
        mass: 9
      - item: bread flour
        mass: 320
      - item: granulated sugar
        mass: 35
      - item: fine sea salt
        mass: 7
      - item: egg
        qty: 1
        unit: ea
      - item: egg yolk
        qty: 1
        unit: ea
      - item: butter
        mass: 42
        note: softened
    steps:
      - warm 120g whole milk to 35°C
      - whisk in 9g instant yeast until dissolved, rest in a warm spot 8 mins
      - in stand mixer bowl, whisk together 320g bread flour, 35g granulated sugar, 7g fine sea salt
      - fit dough hook, turn to low
      - slowly stream in milk/yeast mixture, mix briefly to combine
      - add tangzhong, 1 egg, 1 egg yolk; mix on medium-low until combined, scraping down sides
      - gradually add 42g softened butter in pieces, fully incorporating before adding more
      - knead on medium-low 5-8 mins until smooth
      - shape into ball, place seam-side down in greased bowl, cover with damp towel
      - proof in a warm spot 1-1.5 hours until doubled
  - name: shaping
    steps:
      - punch dough down, turn onto lightly floured surface
      - divide into 6 pieces, ~95-105g each
      - 'for each piece: stretch and fold edges toward centre, flip seam-side down'
      - drag dough toward you keeping contact with the board to build tension; rotate 90°, repeat around the perimeter until a tight smooth ball forms
  - name: second proof
    steps:
      - place on greased parchment-lined tray with 6cm between buns
      - cover with an inverted tray to prevent drying
      - proof at room temp 1-2 hours until doubled
  - name: baking
    ingredients:
      - item: egg
        qty: 1
        unit: ea
        note: for egg wash, whisked with a splash of milk
      - item: milk
        note: a splash, for egg wash
      - item: melted butter
        note: for brushing after baking
    steps:
      - preheat oven to 190°C
      - whisk 1 egg with a splash of milk; brush tops of buns
      - bake 16-18 mins until deeply golden
      - immediately brush generously with melted butter
      - cool completely on rack before slicing
